Colombia Army Kills FARC Leader Bocanegra, Espectador Reports

-- B y   R o d r i g o   O r i h u e l a
-- 
2011-06-04T14:24:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-04/colombia-army-kills-farc-leader-bocanegra-espectador-reports.html
Colombia ’s army killed Alirio Rojas
Bocanegra, head of security for the leader of the Revolutionary
Armed Forces of Colombia, known as FARC, newspaper El Espectador
reported, without saying how it obtained the information.  Bocanegra, known as “El Abuelo,” was killed with two
other rebel leaders, the daily said. Yesterday, President Juan Manuel Santos wrote in his Twitter account that “a blow was
given” to the rebel group, lead by Alfonso Cano, the paper
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rodrigo Orihuela in  Buenos Aires  at 
 rorihuela@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
